I think this is a bit hacky, instead, can we just issue one shutdown(), don't worry about the result of it (since we know it is going to succeed even if it runs into ZK issues) and then just join on the master thread? That means the code will look like this..
master.start()
htu.waitFor(.... masterThread.getMaster().serverMgr() != null);
Thread.run() {
conn.getAdmin().shutdown();
// don't worry about the return value
}
masterThread.join()
shutdownThread.join()
Thoughts?

